snippet.textDisplay:
On the topic of "Series X" I think we're going to see modular components for the console. My prediction is they're not going to be selling an "Elite" version of the console for longer than normal. And you're going to see a VR and Kinect-like modules that can be swapped out over the years with different models etc. Means they can sell more hardware. This is what Nintendo has been successful doing and Microsoft is going to copy it. The controller needs to get rid of that hybrid D-Pad. It's less finessed than the regular cross D-Pad. Using an elite controller made it obvious that the old cross D-Pad is superior. And the specs sound good on paper - when don't they? But I'm very doubtful that's the actual in-engine graphics of Hellblade 2. It looks like pre-rendered cinematics - it's just a video.
EDIT: Would love to know the price. We can be pretty confident it's at least $499. And judging by the overkill specs it's probably more like $599 or higher.
